  <div class="sidebar-box">
    <div class="sidebar-box__wrapper">

      <div class="projects-list projects-list--current-projects">
        <h2 class="projects-list__header">Current Projects</h2>
        <% data.projects.each do |project| %>
          <article class="projects-list__project">
            <% link_to "/projects/#{project[0]}" do %>
              <div class="projects-list__project__logo <%= project[0] %>" style="background-image: url(/images/<%= project[1].logo %>)"></div>
            <% end %>
            <div class="projects-list__project__text">
              <% link_to "/projects/#{project[0]}" do %>
              <h3 class="projects-list__project__name"><%= project[1].name %></h3>
              <% end %>
              <span class="projects-list__project__tagline"><%= project[1].tagline %></span>
            </div>
          </article>
        <% end %>
      </div>

      <aside class="choose-project">
        <h2>What Makes a Good CUSD Project?</h2>

        <div class="accordion">
          <h3 class="accordion__header">A Meaningful Student Experience</h3>
          <div class="accordion__content">
            <p>[LOREM] Ideally we look for a stakeholder that has an existing, positive relationship with the community, but has few financial resources to otherwise make the project happen without pro bono services.</p>
            <p>The stakeholder’s mission should be aligned with the tangible aims of CUSD, and they should know exactly what they need from CUSD, but be open to creativity and ambition.</p>
            <p>Finally, the ideal stakeholder has proven experience and the means to be successful, plus is willing and able to serve as a mentor throughout the project.</p>  
